#!/usr/bin/perl
use strict;
use warnings;
use Mason::App;
Mason::App->run();

__END__

=head1 NAME

mason - evaluate a mason template and output the result

=head1 SYNOPSIS

   # Evaluate template from STDIN
   mason [mason options] [--args json-string]

   # Evaluate template in file
   mason [mason options] [--args json-string] template-file

=head1 DESCRIPTION

Reads a Mason template (component) from STDIN or a file, runs it and outputs
the result to STDOUT.

=head1 MASON OPTIONS

Any Mason options can be specified on the command line and will be passed to
Mason->new, via L<MooseX::Getopt|MooseX::Getopt>. e.g.

    --comp_root /path/to/comp_root --data_dir /path/to/data_dir
    --plugins MyPlugin --plugins MyOtherPlugin

By default C<comp_root> will be set to the directory of the template file, or
to a temporary directory if using STDIN, and C<data_dir> will be set to a
temporary directory.

=head1 ADDITIONAL OPTIONS

=over

=item --args json-string

A list of arguments to pass to the component, in JSON form. e.g.

    --args '["count",5,"names",["Alice","Bob"]]'

=back

=head1 AUTHOR

Jonathan Swartz

=head1 SEE ALSO

L<Mason|Mason>

=cut
